The article emphasizes the importance of the right to vote in shaping the future of the United States. It highlights the current attacks on voting rights, with bills in state legislatures that seek to limit early voting and vote by mail, making it harder for people to vote. The author argues that these attacks are meant to silence certain Americans but have an impact on all Americans. Despite the setback in the Senate, the author, along with the President, remains determined to strengthen voting rights. They plan to fortify and expand the coalition on voting rights, promote voter engagement and registration, and work with Congress to pass legislation such as the For The People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. The article concludes by stating that the right to vote is an American right and that it is everyone's duty to protect and strengthen it.